25/03/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A delegation from the European Parliament visited Croatia on Monday (24 March) to discuss the country's application for accession talks with the EU.
The leader of the delegation, Doris Pack, met with Deputy Foreign Minister Ivan Simonovic, sharing views on Croatia's relations with the UN war crimes tribunal and the conflict in Iraq.
Iraq was also the subject of a meeting Monday between Prime Minister Ivica Racan and US Ambassador to Croatia Lawrence Rossin.
It followed reports in the local press about disagreements possibly damaging bilateral relations.
Zagreb has agreed to provide logistical support to the US-led operations in Iraq.
(Vjesnik, Vecernji List - 25/03/03;
HINA - 24/03/03)
